title: header()
brief: Return the value of an email header.
seealso: body, all_headers
version: 0.07
----

<p>When in message-mode, or index-mode, the <span class="tt">header()</span> function may be used to retrieve the value of a given header in the currently selected message.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre>
<a href="msg.html">msg</a>( "This mail has subject" .. header( "Subject" ) );
</pre>
